{{Infobox organization | image = Coat of Arms of ASALE.svg | alt = A shield with a helmet on top and flowing ribbons around it, surrounded by the flags of the member states. On the shield is a flame down the middle with a castle on the top-left, map of Latin America on the bottom-left, Colombus' three ships on the top-right, and a lion on the bottom-right. Below is a ribbon reading "{{lang|es|UNA ESTIRPE·UNA LENGUA Y UN DESTINO}}" | caption = | map = Países con academia de la lengua española.png | motto = "{{lang|es|Una estirpe, una lengua y un destino}}" ("One lineage, one language, and one destiny") | predecessor = | successor = | formation = {{start date|1951}} | extinction = <!-- date of extinction, optional --> | type = <!-- [[Governmental organization|GO]], [[Non-governmental organization|NGO]], [[Intergovernmental organization|IGO]], [[International nongovernmental organization|INGO]], etc --> | status = <!-- ad hoc, treaty, foundation, etc --> | purpose = <!-- focus as e.g. humanitarian, peacekeeping, etc --> | headquarters = [[Madrid]], [[Spain]] | coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> | language = [[Spanish language|Spanish]] | leader_title = President | leader_name = Darío Villanueva | leader_title2 = General Secretary | leader_name2 = Francisco Javier Pérez | leader_name3 = | leader_title3 = | leader_title4 = | leader_name4 = | key_people = | main_organ = Permanent commission | parent_organization = <!-- if one --> | affiliations = <!-- if any --> | budget = | remarks = | name = Association of Academies of the Spanish Language | bgcolor = <!-- header background color --> | fgcolor = <!-- header text color --> | image_border = | size = <!-- default 140px --> | msize = 300px | malt = <!-- map alt text --> | mcaption = Countries where Spanish-language academies exist. | map2 = | abbreviation = {{lang|es|ASALE}} | location = | region_served = | membership = | general = <!-- Secretary General --> | num_staff = | num_volunteers = | website = {{URL|http://www.asale.org}} | former name = }} {{Spanish language}} The '''Association of Academies of the Spanish Language''' ({{lang-es|Asociación de Academias de la Lengua Española}}, ASALE) is an entity whose end is to work for the unity, integrity, and growth of the [[Spanish language]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.asale.org/sites/default/files/Estatutos_ASALE_2007.pdf|title=Estatutos y reglamento de la Asociación de Academias de la Lengua Española|last=|first=|date=2007|website=ASALE|trans-title=Statutes and regulation of the Association of Academies of the Spanish Language|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170918063651/http://www.asale.org/sites/default/files/Estatutos_ASALE_2007.pdf|archive-date=18 September 2017|dead-url=no|access-date=14 June 2018}}</ref> It was created in [[Mexico]] in 1951 and represents the union of all the separate academies in the Spanish-speaking world. The association publishes reference works on the Spanish language and commemorative editions of Hispanic literature, among other publications.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.asale.org/obras-y-proyectos|title=Obras y proyectos|last=|first=|date=|website=Asociación de Academias de la Lengua Española|archive-url=https://archive.is/20171103030927/http://www.asale.org/obras-y-proyectos|archive-date=2017-11-03|dead-url=yes|access-date=Nov 3, 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.asale.org/publicaciones|title=Publicaciones|last=|first=|date=|website=Asociación de Academias de la Lengua Española|archive-url=https://archive.is/20171103031646/http://www.asale.org/publicaciones|archive-date=2017-11-03|dead-url=yes|access-date=Nov 3, 2017|df=}}</ref>
==History== Through the initiative of then-president of Mexico [[Miguel Alemán Valdés]], the first congress of academies convened with the purpose of maintaining the integrity of and fostering the further growth of Spanish.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://www.asale.org/la-asociacion/actividad-institucional/i-congreso-mexico-1951|title=I Congreso (México, 1951)|last=|first=|date=|website=Asociación de Academias de la Lengua Española|archive-url=https://archive.is/20171101071759/http://www.asale.org/la-asociacion/actividad-institucional/i-congreso-mexico-1951|archive-date=1 November 2017|dead-url=yes|access-date=1 November 2017}}</ref> The meeting was held from 23 April to 6 May 1951 and resulted in the creation of the association<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.asale.org/la-asociacion/politica-panhispanica/siglo-xx|title=Siglo XX|last=|first=|date=|website=Asociación de Academias de la Lengua Española|archive-url=https://archive.is/20171101072747/http://www.asale.org/la-asociacion/politica-panhispanica/siglo-xx|archive-date=1 November 2017|dead-url=yes|access-date=1 November 2017}}</ref> and its permanent commission<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.asale.org/la-asociacion/politica-linguistica-panhispanica/hechos-relevantes|title=Historia|last=|first=|date=|website=Asociación de Academias de la Lengua Española|archive-url=https://archive.is/20171101073040/http://www.asale.org/la-asociacion/politica-linguistica-panhispanica/hechos-relevantes|archive-date=1 November 2017|dead-url=yes|access-date=1 November 2017}}</ref>. The [[Royal Spanish Academy]] (Spanish: {{lang|es|Real Academia Española}} or {{Lang|es|RAE}}) was not present at the initial meeting but participated in the permanent commission.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.asale.org/la-asociacion/politica-linguistica-panhispanica/hechos-relevantes|title=Historia|last=|first=|date=|website=Asociación de Academias de la Lengua Española|archive-url=https://archive.is/20171101073040/http://www.asale.org/la-asociacion/politica-linguistica-panhispanica/hechos-relevantes|archive-date=1 November 2017|dead-url=yes|access-date=1 November 2017}}</ref> Ever since the second congress convened in 1956, the {{Lang|es|RAE}} has been a regular participant.{{Citation needed|date=October 2017}}
In 2000 the association organised the School of Hispanic Lexicography and the Carolina Foundation to promote Spanish lexicography{{Citation needed|date=November 2017}}, and together with the {{Lang|es|RAE}}, the association earned the [[Prince of Asturias Awards|Prince of Asturias Award]] for peace.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.asale.org/la-asociacion/politica-panhispanica/siglo-xx|title=Siglo XX|last=|first=|date=|website=Asociación de Academias de la Lengua Española|archive-url=https://archive.is/20171101072747/http://www.asale.org/la-asociacion/politica-panhispanica/siglo-xx|archive-date=1 November 2017|dead-url=yes|access-date=1 November 2017}}</ref>
An academy for [[Equatorial Guinea]] was created in 2013 and joined the association in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.asale.org/noticias/aprobada-la-incorporacion-de-la-academia-ecuatoguineana-la-asale-0|title=Aprobada la incorporación de la Academia Ecuatoguineana a la ASALE|last=|first=|date=19 March 2017|website=Asociación de Academias de la Lengua Española|archive-url=https://archive.is/20160327014050/http://www.asale.org/noticias/aprobada-la-incorporacion-de-la-academia-ecuatoguineana-la-asale-0|archive-date=27 March 2016|dead-url=yes|access-date=1 November 2017}}</ref>
