{{Politics of Portugal}} The '''Council of Ministers''' ({{lang-pt|Conselho de Ministros}}, {{IPA-pt|kõˈseʎu dɨ miˈniʃtɾuʃ|pron}} or {{IPA-pt|kõˈsɐʎu dɨ mɨˈniʃtɾuʃ|}}) is a [[collegial]] [[executive body]] within the [[Government of Portugal]]. It is presided over by the [[Prime Minister of Portugal|Prime Minister]], but the [[President of Portugal]] can take on this role at the Prime Minister's request. All senior ministers are members of the council of ministers, and when the prime minister finds it applicable, state secretaries can also attend its meetings.
== Functions ==
The Council of Ministers discusses and approves [[Bill (proposed law)|bills]] to be submitted to the [[Assembly of the Republic (Portugal)|Assembly of the Republic]] and [[decree]]s and resolutions.
