'''Roberto Kozak''' (14 May 1942 &ndash; September 2015) was an [[Argentina|Argentinian]] diplomat and humanitarian, of Ukrainian descent, notable for his work to rescue people from the [[Human rights violations in Pinochet's Chile|prisons and death squads]] of the [[Augusto Pinochet|Chilean military dictatorship]].<ref name="guardian">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/dec/14/roberto-kozak-chile-latin-america-schindler|title=Latin America’s Schindler: a forgotten hero of the 20th century|date=14 December 2016|publisher=|via=The Guardian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03z6238|title=My Father Saved 30,000 People in Chile|work=[[BBC World Service]]|date=1 Jul 2016}}</ref> Kozak was a recipient of the [[Order of Bernardo O'Higgins]] with the rank Grand Cross, Chile's highest honour for non-Chilean civilians.<ref name="guardian" /><ref name="museo">{{cite web|url=http://www.archivomuseodelamemoria.cl/index.php/80094;isad|title=Item 000002 - Intervención del señor Roberto Kozak en la ceremonia de condecoración con la orden de Bernardo O ´Higgins. - Archivo de Fondos y Colecciones|publisher=}}</ref>
